<section id="commands.groups.image"><title>Image Commands</title>
	
	<para>Save bitmap and vector images of the current view. The GUI is not required in order to save images -- using these commands from the command-line, for example, works just as well (models still have a current view, even without the GUI, and can be rotated, translated etc. just as if they were in the GUI).</para>

	<section id="command.ref.savebitmap"><title>savebitmap</title>
		<indexterm><primary>commands</primary><secondary>savebitmap</secondary></indexterm>
		
		<para><emphasis>Syntax:</emphasis></para>
		<funcsynopsis>
			<funcprototype>
				<funcdef>void <function>savebitmap</function></funcdef>
				<paramdef>string <parameter>format</parameter></paramdef>
				<paramdef>string <parameter>filename</parameter></paramdef>
			</funcprototype>
			<funcprototype>
				<funcdef>void <function>savebitmap</function></funcdef>
				<paramdef>string <parameter>format</parameter></paramdef>
				<paramdef>string <parameter>filename</parameter></paramdef>
				<paramdef>int <parameter>width</parameter></paramdef>
				<paramdef>int <parameter>height</parameter></paramdef>
			</funcprototype>
			<funcprototype>
				<funcdef>void <function>savebitmap</function></funcdef>
				<paramdef>string <parameter>format</parameter></paramdef>
				<paramdef>string <parameter>filename</parameter></paramdef>
				<paramdef>int <parameter>width</parameter></paramdef>
				<paramdef>int <parameter>height</parameter></paramdef>
				<paramdef>int <parameter>quality</parameter></paramdef>
			</funcprototype>
		</funcsynopsis>
		
		<para>Saves the current view as a bitmap image. Allowable values for <emphasis>format</emphasis> are:</para>
		<table frame='all' pgwide='1' tocentry='0'><title>Bitmap image formats</title>
			<tgroup cols='2' align='left' colsep='1' rowsep='1'>
				<thead>
					<row>
						<entry>Shortname</entry>
						<entry>Format</entry>
					</row>
				</thead>
				<tbody>
					<row>
						<entry>bmp</entry>
						<entry>Windows Bitmap</entry>
					</row>
					<row>
						<entry>jpg</entry>
						<entry>Joint Photographic Experts Group</entry>
					</row>
					<row>
						<entry>png</entry>
						<entry>Portable Network Graphic</entry>
					</row>
					<row>
						<entry>ppm</entry>
						<entry>Portable Pixmap</entry>
					</row>
					<row>
						<entry>xbm</entry>
						<entry>X11 Bitmap</entry>
					</row>
					<row>
						<entry>xpm</entry>
						<entry>X11 Pixmap</entry>
					</row>
				</tbody>
			</tgroup>
		</table>
		
		<para>If <emphasis>width</emphasis> and <emphasis>height</emphasis> are not specified the current dimensions of the view are used (800x600 if no GUI is present). The <emphasis>quality</emphasis> option determines the compression used on saved images, affecting, for example, the quality and size of jpegs and pngs, and should be an integer between 1 and 100 (with 100 being the best compression).</para>
		
		<para>For example:</para>
		<synopsis>
			savebitmap(&quot;bmp&quot;, &quot;test.bmp&quot;);
		</synopsis>
		<para>saves the current view to a file 'test.bmp'.</para>
		<synopsis>
			savebitmap(&quot;png&quot;, &quot;big.png&quot;, 5000, 5000, 10);
		</synopsis>
		<para>saves an enormous, highly uncompressed png.</para>

	</section>
	
</section>
